.TH "regmap_test_bits" 9 "regmap_test_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regmap_test_bits \- Check if all specified bits are set in a register.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regmap_test_bits
.BI "(struct regmap *map "  ","
.BI "unsigned int reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int bits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map" 12
Register map to operate on
.IP "reg" 12
Register to read from
.IP "bits" 12
Bits to test
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if at least one of the tested bits is not set, 1 if all tested
bits are set and a negative error number if the underlying \fBregmap_read\fP
fails.
